vectorData.altText: 5. The _______________ nerve is associated with extension of the elbow, wrist, thumb and digits.
That's right!  The radial nerve innervates all muscle of the posterior compartment of arm and forearm, therefore it is associated with extension of the elbow, wrist, thumb and digits.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

The radial nerve continues from the posterior compartment of the arm into the posterior compartment of the forearm. It innervates all muscles of this compartment, and therefore is responsible for extension of the wrist, thumb and fingers.
Its superficial branch is cutaneous to the dorsolateral aspect of the hand (green).
Do you recall what a “drop wrist” is? How does it present?
In Exercise 17.2, you will learn further details about the motor and sensory innervation of the hand.
